post_text:
When you attend a POUND class with POUND Tour Crew member, Lisa McManes, you get an awesome workout that uses lightly weighted drumsticks called RIPSTIX to create resistance as you drum along to the beat of different music genres.

You get a full body workout through cardio, strength, isometric and Pilates based movements. Modifications are always demonstrated and all fitness levels are welcome.

Lisa has been a POUND Pro for over 3 years, a member of POUND Tour Crew for over a year and is also trained in AMPLIFY, Level Up and Generation POUND. Lisa has been certified Personal Trainer with the National Academy Of Sports Medicine for over 8 years.

Check out the events section of this page for all the fantastic options & locations for classes & events. Lisa feels it is a great workout for your body, mind & soul. ⚡️

⚡️You BECOME part of the music in POUND.

https://youtu.be/gGh4-GpcV8M

I just wanted to send a big thank you to all of my clients, family and friends. I really appreciated your support the past few months as I tried to navigate the whole Covid situation with my small business. It was a rough start with lots of tears. Without you rallying behind MPT we would not have been successful. I am glad we found a way for us all to support, inspire and motivate each other while we stayed safe at home.

Next week I am starting to slowly take my clients off virtual and bringing them back in person. I also have some staying virtual and have added new clients virtually from other cities & states. I feel so blessed that my business is even stronger and that I am able to help…

post_text:
When you attend a POUND® class with POUND® TOUR CREW member Lisa McManes, you get an awesome 45 minute workout that uses lightly weighted drumsticks called RIPSTIX to create resistance as you drum along to the beat of different music genres.

You get a full body workout through cardio, strength, isometric and Pilates based movements. Modifications are always demonstrated and all fitness levels are welcome.

Come check out a real POUND® class. Do not be fooled by other imitation pounding/drumming fitness classes.

⚡️You BECOME part of the music in POUND.

post_text:
People are asking about in-person trainings and group classes. Currently the step-by-step process to reopen businesses in Ohio does not include gyms at this time. I understand the need to follow the continued COVID-19 outbreaks to better determine what our protection requirements will be as the state moves forward.

However, even if gyms open this month, McManes Personal Training will stay virtual for all trainings & group classes the remainder￼ of May. The process of physical training & group classes will be re-evaluated in June.

There are lots of opportunities to workout in ZOOM with an awesome group of supportive people and myself right now while gyms are closed. I also have my 4 week customized virtual program available for purchase so you can workout at home on your own time. Current clients are still having 1:1 trainings on ZOOM with me.

Watch this page for class details.

I miss you all and hope to see you soon.
Please continue to stay safe and well!

post_text:
This MBSR guided meditation will be a repeat of the “library” that I did a few weeks ago dueto popular demand to have it repeated. You may want a journal or paper to jot down any thoughts and feelings at the end of the meditation.

During this 30 minute class we will practice a mind-body meditative practice to help you draw upon your inner resources for greater health, balance, and peace of mind.

This practice can help you:
* Approach your life with more composure, energy, understanding and enthusiasm.
* Develop the ability to cope more effectively with both short-term and long-term stressful situations.
* Improve your focus

post_text:
Some of you have inquired about my MBSR class and my certification. All classes will currently be on ZOOM and events can be found on this page.

Feel free to share those events with anyone you feel might enjoy the 30 minute class.

I am a certified Meditation Trainer in Mindfulness Based Stress Reduction from the University Of Massachusetts Medical School. I am also a Certified Personal Trainer with the National Academy Of Sports Medicine.

Each 30 minute class will be slightly different as we practice different mind-body meditative practices and principles to help you draw upon your inner resources for greater health, balance, and peace of mind.

* Approach your life with more composure, energy, understanding and enthusiasm
* Develop the ability to cope more effectively with both short-term and long-term stressful situations
* Improve your focus

post_text:
Here is a quick workout you can do at home with no equipment.

3 Rounds, 1 minute active break (tap feet side to side, move arms, etc.. ) between your full rounds.

1 minute of jumping jacks, 20 squats (or squat jumps), 20 alternating forward lunges, 20 burpees, hold a 60 second hand plank, 20 mountain climbers, 20 knee bent crunches, hold a 60 second elbow plank, 1 minute of high knees.

shared_text:
POUNDFIT.COM
BORN TO REBEL

POUND - Rockout. Workout.
January 16 at 10:00 AM ·

POUND was born out of a rebellious spirit. We’ve always believed in Doing It Different—fitting into a box was never the goal. And like any purpose-driven company, we were sparked from a problem we saw seeping from the gym environment.

In a world where experiences can be intimidating and exclusive, profit is often prioritized before people and calorie counting, “problem areas” and before + after pictures are the standard, POUND believed the fitness industry could do better.

Starting this journey as a company was, to say the least,
a rebellious act.

It shouldn’t be about the rules, approvals, and standards society places on us. It shouldn’t drain your soul.

We believe fitness is a journey,…

post_text:
With crazy weather approaching in the next month or two, I wanted to post about classes.

🥶If I do not already have your cell phone, please direct message it to me if you want added to the text alerts about class cancellations due to weather. I will also post any cancellations on this page as well🥶

❄️ Please make sure you are not wearing wet boots/shoes onto the classroom floor. If you choose to wear shoes in class instead of going barefoot , please change into dry shoes.

☃️ If Lexington Local Schools are canceled, then morning classes at No Limits will be canceled. If Richland County is under a level 2, classes will be cancelled.

Any questions, feel free to message or text me.

My 1:1 Personal Training still has a waiting list. However, you can still train with me. I have some spots open in my virtual programs. My virtual clients love being able to exercise when it fits into their schedule. Those that travel for work love being able to access their programs wherever they are.

Message me for more details.
💪🏻💪🏻💪🏻💪🏻

Virtual Lifestyle/Accountability Coaching: $150 1 month session. Goal setting, challenges, motivational texts/emails, virtual weigh in and/measurements. Additional 1:1 check in (face to face or phone call) as needed for additional $25 per hour session.

On-line Fitness program: $175 Custom designed 3 month program. Individual on-line calendar with workouts created for you. There are written instructions and video demonstrations that you click on to see how to do the exercise. I base this off your goals, your assessment with me & what equipment you have to use at home or a gym. I have a lot of people who like this, as they can exercise when they have time and especially if they travel for work, they can take their workout with them.
